Source code:
~~~js
function uniqueId(prefix='$lodash$') {
  if (!idCounter[prefix]) {
    idCounter[prefix] = 0
  }

  const id =++idCounter[prefix]
  if (prefix === '$lodash$') {
    return `${id}`
  }

  return `${prefix + id}`
}
~~~

`$lodash$` will be used as the default prefix if the parameter is empty. 
If manually use `$lodash$` as the input, the generated id will not contains the prefix.

~~~js
uniqueId('$lodash$'); // 1. It should output $lodash$1
~~~

